### [Psalms Chapter 13](../../../bib/kjv/psa013.htm#001.md)

[Psalms 13:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa013.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">psa 13:2</span></span>

How long - Shall I be in such perplexities, not knowing what course to
take?

[Psalms 13:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa013.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">psa 13:3</span></span>

Lighten - Revive and comfort, and deliver me from the darkness of death,
which is ready to come upon me.

[Psalms 13:6](../../../bib/kjv/psa013.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">psa 13:6</span></span>

I will sing - It is a common thing for David and other prophets to speak
of future deliverances as if they were already come, that so they may
signify both the infallible certainty of the thing, and their firm
assurance thereof.

